---
// Parity port of legacy static `privacy-policy/index.html`.
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Privacy Policy | MFD Research</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for MFD Research website and inquiries." />
  <meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy" content="default-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src https://fonts.gstatic.com; script-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data: https://mfdresearch.com; connect-src 'self';" />
  
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../style.css">
  <style>
    body {
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text-primary);
      line-height: 1.65;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0;
    }
    .wrap {
      max-width: 860px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 32px 20px 64px;
    }
    .top {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 14px;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: var(--navy);
    }
    .top img {
      width: 46px;
      height: 46px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .legal-card {
      background: var(--bg-white);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: 40px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    }
    h1 {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-size: 2.25rem;
      color: var(--navy);
      font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    }
    h2 {
      margin: 32px 0 12px;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      color: var(--navy);
      font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    }
    p, li { color: var(--text-secondary); }
    ul { padding-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
    li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .meta {
      margin-top: 0;
      color: var(--green);
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    .home-btn {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 32px;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: #fff;
      background: var(--navy);
      border-radius: 99px;
      padding: 12px 24px;
      font-weight: 600;
      transition: transform 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
    }
    .home-btn:hover {
      background: var(--navy-light);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main class="wrap">
    <a class="top" href="../" aria-label="Return to home page">
      <img src="../assets/mfd-logo.jpg" alt="MFD Research logo" />
      <strong>MFD Research</strong>
    </a>

    <article class="legal-card">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: March 6, 2026</p>

      <p>
        MFD Research respects your privacy. This policy explains what information we collect on this website,
        how we use it, and how we protect it.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Contact details you submit, such as name, email address, company, and message content.</li>
        <li>Basic technical information such as browser type and device details collected by standard web hosting tools.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To respond to inquiries and provide consulting information.</li>
        <li>To improve website performance, usability, and security.</li>
        <li>To maintain business records related to inbound requests.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell personal information. We may share data with service providers that help us host the site,
        process form submissions, or maintain operations, subject to confidentiality obligations.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We keep inquiry data only as long as necessary for business, legal, or operational purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Choices</h2>
      <p>
        You may request access, correction, or deletion of your submitted personal information by contacting us at
        <a href="mailto:info@mfdresearch.com">info@mfdresearch.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Policy Updates</h2>
      <p>
        We may revise this policy from time to time. Updates will be posted on this page with a new effective date.
      </p>

      <a class="home-btn" href="../">Back to Home</a>
    </article>
  </main>
</body>
</html>

